PURSUANT to Section 44(2) of the County Governments Act (Cap. 265), a person shall be qualified for appointment as County Secretary if that person:
is a citizen of Kenya;
holds a degree from a university recognized in Kenya;
has at least ten (10) years relevant professional experience;
has at least five (5) yearsâ€™ experience in a leadership position at senior management level in a public service or private sector organization; and
meets the requirements of leadership and integrity as prescribed in Chapter Six of the Constitution.
Terms of Service: Six (6) Year Contract. Remuneration: As determined by the Salaries and Remuneration Commission (SRC).
